<article>
    <h1>On so&#xAD;cial me&#xAD;dia</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200907/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-07"><time>2020-09-07</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE TRENDING</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>SHAM­POO SPOOF: If there is to be a Hong Kong ver­sion of hit K-drama The World Of The Mar­ried, ac­tors Kevin Cheng and Grace Chan can surely be con­sid­ered.</p>
    <p>The celebrity cou­ple looked the part when they filmed a sham­poo ad­ver­tise­ment (above left) and spoofed a poster fea­tur­ing the leads Park Hae-joon and Kim</p>
    <p>Hee-ae (above right). The South Korean TV se­ries, which is also called A World Of Mar­ried Cou­ple, is a show about mar­i­tal in­fi­delity and an adap­ta­tion of the BBC drama Doc­tor Foster (2015 to present).</p>
    <p>Cheng, 51, and Chan, 29, mar­ried in 2018 and have two sons – Rafael, who was born in Fe­bru­ary last year, and Yan­nick, born in July.</p>
    <p>In a video of the ad­ver­tise­ment posted on so­cial me­dia last Fri­day, Chan wrote: “Did you watch the pop­u­lar K-drama The World Of The Mar­ried? There was an un­for­get­table scene where the woman found a strand of hair, which was not hers, on her hus­band.</p>
    <p>“But our ver­sion is dif­fer­ent.</p>
    <p>I was very wor­ried when I suf­fered hair loss dur­ing my preg­nancy... How­ever, af­ter the first ex­pe­ri­ence, I knew how to take care of my hair dur­ing my sec­ond preg­nancy.</p>
    <p>“If you see my hus­band’s ex­pres­sion, you will know: Hair loss? Noth­ing to be afraid of.”</p>
    <p>Cheng posted a photo of the spoofed poster on so­cial me­dia, where he was seen car­ry­ing a bot­tle of sham­poo while hold­ing his wife’s leg, em­u­lat­ing Park’s char­ac­ter. He wrote: “Don’t be wor­ried, my wife. Only one strand of hair has fallen. I know how to deal with it.”</p>
    <p>This is the first time Cheng and Chan, who met on the set of su­per­nat­u­ral TV drama Blue Veins in 2016, have filmed an ad­ver­tise­ment to­gether.</p>

